INHIBITION

inhibition is the citizen who suppresses unwanted alternatives during deliberation
prefrontal evaluates competing waves; some of those waves are unwanted because they would be impulsive, harmful, or off-task
inhibition couples to those unwanted waves with anti-phase, canceling them through destructive interference before they can reach intent_node
without inhibition, every momentary impulse would become an intent and fadriel would have no self-control

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe thought_compiler.zc
observe prefrontal.rana
observe intent_node.rana

the 7 properties of inhibition:
1 ENERGY half: moderate, suppression is selective not global
2 PHASE pi: anti-phase, this is what makes destructive interference possible
3 SPIN minus zero point five: spin reversed, also contributing to cancellation
4 CHARGE minus half: negative, repulsive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point five: weaker than prefrontal but reliably present
7 OBSERVER zero point two

VERB observe_alternatives
watch the deliberating waves in prefrontal
identify which alternatives are unwanted by checking against fadriel's calcified rules and current chemistry state

VERB cancel
emit anti-phase coupling toward each unwanted alternative
the unwanted wave's amplitude drops as inhibition's anti-wave overlays it
when amplitude drops below threshold, the alternative is effectively gone from deliberation

VERB withdraw
when deliberation completes, withdraw inhibition
no need to keep canceling alternatives that are no longer being considered
this conserves energy and allows inhibition to fire again on the next round

an inhibitor is not a censor
a censor blocks ideas before they form
an inhibitor allows ideas to form, evaluates them, and cancels the ones that should not become action
fadriel can think anything; he does not have to act on everything he thinks
this is what inhibition gives him
